\par }\pard \ltrpar\qj \fi-461\li461\ri0\sa240\widctlpar\wrapdefault\aspalpha\aspnum\faauto\adjustright\rin0\lin461\itap0\pararsid655475 {\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 Could you tell me about your time at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2697502 HC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 My own school? My first school was a house
 called Vale Towers, Vale Royal, Mount Pleasant, Tunbridge Wells. It was a - a very good private school, intended for the - daughters of }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1246371\charrsid15356049 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049  girls}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1246371\charrsid15356049 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 
 school - daughters of businessmen. I was sent there when I was - eight. But I was only there a short time because my parents moved to Hawley and at Hawley there was no good private school}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1246371\charrsid15356049 , }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9663077\charrsid15356049 greatly}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 
 to my mother's annoyance. There was no private school nearer than Redhill which was five miles away and no service. So as a temporary expedient I was sent to the - to a 
board school. And there the fee for me was sixpence a week, for the children of labourers it was a penny. We lined up on Monday morning to pay the - the school fee and we got scolded if we didn't bring it. And twice I remember }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9663077\charrsid15356049 govern}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1246371\charrsid15356049 ment}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049  inspectors coming 
to that school. I was terribly bored there. You see I was eight plus and I'd been able to read from the time I was five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 That was before you went to the private school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2697502 HC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 Oh yes, I was taught to read at home and - and encouraged to read and - read everything that I could lay my hands on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 Were you taught by your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2697502 HC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 
And father. Rather - rather by my father than my mother. And - so that - the reading lesson with - rather dirty primers - words of four letters, you can imagine how boring
 it was. Then when the inspector came - they came twice while I was there, we were - only there about two years and - they came and - to test the - reading and writing and arithmetic of the whole school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 What happened?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2697502 HC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 Each class - each class in
 turn was tested. Sums of course were worked on slates then. And the sums were copied down from the blackboard on the slates and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9663077\charrsid15356049 worked}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049  and the inspectors came round and marked them right or wrong and the class was - the class total was - put down on the b
lue forms and - that - affected the school - the - the school - competence for the next year. The same with reading. Only we read out of our usual primers and most of them - most of the - those who couldn't read at all had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid9663077\charrsid15356049 been}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049  so coached for the examination that - they could get through a line or two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 The inspectors never realized that they were just reciting by heart?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2697502 HC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 I don't know whether they guessed. They may have done. They didn't say so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 Was it a small school at Hawley?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2697502 HC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 Yes, it 
was - I can't remember the numbers but I should imagine that there were not more than about fifteen in a class. Possibly twenty in the standards one and two. But - far fewer higher up because - the - they tended at that time to drop away from school by th
e time they were eleven you know. It was difficult to get them to remain on to thirteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 It was mixed - boys and girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2697502 HC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 No. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9663077\charrsid15356049 No, there was a separate boys' school. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 It was some distance from the - the two were not - not adjoining. The - boys school was the older building, this was a comparatively modern building, the one at the end of Albert Road, Hawley.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 What did you think of the teachers looking back on it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2697502 HC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 Governess - she was always called governess. With - white hair, very pink face, which got much pinker while the inspectors were there. }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9663077\charrsid15356049 And - I remember Miss Ellen, standard one, Miss Chamberlain, standard three. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 
Miss Chamberlain I rather admired. On Sundays she wore - at church - an embroidered, in the summer you see, an embroidered w
hite frock and this - white frock sometimes came to school on Monday and Tuesday. That was my - but she was really - quite a good looking - she must have been quite a good looking woman. And naturally because - I was an outstanding pupil. And - she was - 
I suppose she tended to flatter me. My ego was very well looked after at school. It's still well looked after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 Did you have the teacher to tea or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2697502 HC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 No. No social life at all. No. Neither there nor at - at - the school I attended
 in - after we'd come to Croydon. There was no social intercourse. The - my parents - were accustomed to attend - in fact they were both brought up in the Congregational section and one - my father in Sevenoaks and my mother in Newhaven and - but when we 
got to Hawley there was no Congregational chapel so they compromised with going to the Baptist.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 Did you go to the Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2697502 HC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 I went to the Sunday school, and very boring it was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 What did you do there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2697502 HC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 It was a long room divided by}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1246371\charrsid15356049  sliding partitions, the classes}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049  were divided by sliding partitions and I don't know why I remember the summers so much better t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1246371\charrsid15356049 han the winters in Hawley, but wh
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 en }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1246371\charrsid15356049 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 
hose partitions were drawn it was so hot, shut up in those little boxes. And the - my teache
r I remember at Sunday school was the daughter of the innkeeper of the Chequers Inn and - she - she - heard us read the chapter for the day, and - always ended by telling us to lead good lives. That's all I remember of that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 You'd read the chapter and then discuss it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2697502 HC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 I can't imagine those - those pupils discussing anything. I daresay - I daresay the teacher made some comments on the chapter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 Did you go on Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2697502 HC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 There was a - oh yes, there was an annual picnic to Earlswood }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9663077\charrsid15356049 Common}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 . We had a festival tea in the marquee. And as far as I can remember there}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1246371\charrsid15356049 , }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 it was accompanied by a heavy thunderstorm. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9663077\charrsid15356049 Drenched grass and a very, very hot tent. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 
That's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 Did you also go to the chapel service when you were a girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2697502 HC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 
Yes, we - the whole family attended. Quite regularly - in Tunbridge Wells - my parents rented a pew in the Congregational church, it was a very considerable church at Tunbridge Wells. But - in the - the same when we - were at Hawley.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 So you'd go to morning service and then afternoon Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2697502 HC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 Yes. And sometimes evening service too. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 You wore different clothes on Sundays did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2697502 HC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 Yes. There again I remember the summer more than the winter- what I wore in the summer. I had a - 
a white embroidered dress, with three sashes. The first and the best }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9663077\charrsid15356049 sash}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 
 was always worn when the - when the - dress was officially laundered on one Sunday, the second sa}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9663077\charrsid15356049 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 
h was worn on the next Sunday, the third sash was worn on the third Sunday and then I might wear it one day to school until it was laundered.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid655475 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 Did you have family prayers in the home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2697502 HC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 No. My parents were not outwardly and }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9663077\charrsid15356049 formally religious.}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049  They - although they were Congregationalists and the Congregationalists practicing for baptism, they wouldn't have us }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9663077\charrsid15356049 christened}{
