 not that he ceased to - to be a Liberal, I should imagine right up to the - as long as he lived he was - he was a very}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1246371\charrsid15356049 ,}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 
 very Liberally minded, and I remember that - from the - he brought even the first numbers of the Strand magazine. I suppose that was - 
must have been - oh yes, that was when I was about nine years old. Yes, it was while we were still at Hawley. The Strand - they came rather close together - the Strand}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid1246371\charrsid15356049 , }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid3767260\charrsid15356049 Tit-Bits, which was the first of its class, and Piersons Weekly. And Answers.
